			<referenceToDataSource type="source data set" refObjectId="70b8b0d9-ae5d-47ee-8537-bc6da4b9d859" uri="../sources/70b8b0d9-ae5d-47ee-8537-bc6da4b9d859.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">Huang, B. et al. Environmental influence assessment of China’s multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) photovoltaic modules considering recycling process. Solar Energy 143, 132–141 (2017).</common:shortDescription>
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="zh">Huang, B. et al. Environmental influence assessment of China’s multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) photovoltaic modules considering recycling process. Solar Energy 143, 132–141 (2017).</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToDataSource>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="en">When utilizing the inventory data for multi-Si PV modules, ensure that the mean values are used if different data sources are encountered for specific materials. This guidance is necessary to maintain consistency and reliability in life cycle assessments. Data sources include academic literature, Environmental Impact Assessment Statements (EIAS), and industry reports pertinent to Chinese photovoltaic enterprises. For detailed LCA modelling, pay attention to geographical and technological relevance, validating and updating the data when applicable to ensure accurate representation of the assessed process.</useAdviceForDataSet>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="zh">在使用多晶硅光伏组件的库存数据时，如果针对特定材料遇到不同的数据来源，请确保使用平均值。这一指导对于保持生命周期评估的一致性和可靠性是必要的。数据来源包括学术文献、环境影响评价报告（EIAS）以及与中国光伏企业相关的行业报告。在详细的生命周期评估建模时，注意地理和技术相关性，适时验证和更新数据以确保所评估过程的准确性。</useAdviceForDataSet>
